<break lines="2"/>

<blurb fontsize="6em">Share-nothing Architecture</blurb>
<list fontsize="3.5em">
<bullet> Like HTTP, each request is distinct</bullet>
<bullet> Shared data is pushed down to the data-store layer</bullet>
<bullet> Avoid front controllers</bullet>
</list>

<break lines="2"/>
<blurb fontsize="6em">This gives us</blurb>
<list fontsize="3.5em">
<bullet> Ability to load balance</bullet>
<bullet> Invisible failover from one datacenter to another</bullet>
<bullet> Better modularization of applications</bullet>
<bullet> Easier to develop and debug</bullet>
</list>
</slide>
